:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">As in: the ability rotate. Used as name for the rotate action button in tactical combat </Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ROTATE_BUTTON</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">DESCRIPTION</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Rotate the unit to change the direction they are facing</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Zmienia kierunek, w którym zwrócona jest jednostka</Data></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">As in: the ability rotate. Used as name for the rotate action button in tactical combat </Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_ERROR</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">NOT_ENOUGH_ESSENCE</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Not enough essence charges</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Za mało ładunków esencji</Data></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicates to the player that they cannot use an ability because the unit does not have the required number of essence charges</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">DAMAGE_TYPES</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ENTROPY</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Entropy</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Entropia</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">DAMAGE_IMMUNITIES</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ENTROPY</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Immune to Entropy</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Niewrażliwość na entropię</Data></Cell></Row><Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0"><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">ABILITY_ERROR</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">AT_MAX_ESSENCE_LINKS</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Unit cannot make any more communion links</Data></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String">Jednostka nie może wytworzyć więcej połączeń zespolenia</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"/></Cell><Cell ss:Index="7"><Data ss:Type="String">In the text below, any inserted strings - anything of the form {text} - is replaced by an integer value for the thing described in the brackets. If the {text} is not followed by a unit - e.g. shields, hitpoints - the icon for the unit is inserted together with the integer. The same holds for symbols - e.g. '+', '%' - which are occasionally inserted together with the integer.</Data></Cell></Row></Table><WorksheetOptions xmlns="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel"><Unsynced/><Selected/><Panes><Pane><Number>3</Number><ActiveRow>31</ActiveRow><ActiveCol>2</ActiveCol></Pane></Panes><ProtectObjects>False</ProtectObjects><ProtectScenarios>False</ProtectScenarios></WorksheetOptions></Worksheet></Workbook>